name: Premier Housewares Adore Pets Lucky Dog Food Storage Bin with Spoon, 6.5 L - Natural
review: I read a number of negative reviews from folks whose tins were damaged in transit or faulty in some way. But I took a chance on this cat food tin. Mine arrived in good time, and is absolutely perfect. The paint is unblemished, nor chips or dents, and the lid is lovely and perfectly snug. There  isn't a rubber seal, but it doesn't need one. All edges are rounded and there are no sharp edges anywhere.I bought the larger of the two sizes available (the 6.5), and I'm glad I did. It holds a goodly amount, around 2.5-3 kg (at a guess, I don't have scales) of my cats' dry food. The tin sits on my counter alongside my toaster and kettle, and is nice to look at, and matches pretty well with my off-white units.I'm very pleased with this purchase.

name: OHMO 3 Pack Dog Food Can Lids, (3, 12, 14oz etc.) Universal Size Silicone Covers for Cat and Dog Food, Dark Blue
review: Three months later the lids are still going strong as new. It takes a second to put it onto a smaller ~70g can, but the 156g fits right away. On both cans the can can be lifted by the lid (even if full) and the lid won't fall off even when shaken lightly. The lids are not airtight so don't expect them to keep the food moist for a long time, but it is good enough for the food to stay fresh for a couple of days. If you've been using plastic bags to keep your open cans in get this instead for sure!The ears are cute but prevent the cans from being stacked on each other. But the ears are cute so I am willing to live with it ^^
